cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with deep neural networks and their compression and acceleration, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and multimedia (cs.MM). Given that the paper focuses on image classification and convolutional neural networks, it is most likely to belong to cs.CV, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. The use of low-rankness and sparsity for network approximation also suggests a possible fit with cs.NE, while the experiments with large datasets and model compression may relate to cs.MM.
